  <div class="presentation__details">
    <h3 class="presentation__title">
      Bring On the WorkerBees (Designing Elixir Systems with OTP)
    </h3>

      <iframe 
        width="560"
        height="315"
        src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/CsmJ_xfzKxw?rel=0"
        frameborder="0"
        allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen>
      </iframe>

    <div class="presentation__description">
        <p>If you want to be a great Elixir developers, you need to learn to build your programs in layers, the way the experts do. In this session, we will explore the advice:</p>
        <p></p>
        <p>Do Fun Things with Big, Loud Workerbees.</p>
        <p></p>
        <p>This sentence, from Designing Elixir Systems with OTP, is a mental mnemonic that stands for Data, Functions, Tests; Boundaries, Lifecycles and Workers. We'll talk about each of these layers in detail focusing on the role of each independent layer in a self-healing, performant Elixir program.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="presentation__bio">
        <p>
          <strong>About Bruce Tate:</strong>
          The founder of Groxio, Bruce Tate is a mountain biker, climber and father of two. He's the co-author of Programming Phoenix, Adopting Elixir and Designing Elixir Systems with OTP. He runs the Programmer Passport program, a subscription service that helps programmers advance by teaching them new programming languages.
        </p>
    </div>
  </div>
